      "content": "i see what you're saying about the long term, but that feels a bit abstract when you're a small business owner facing huge bills next month. it seems like the \"benefits\" you're mentioning are mostly theoretical or social, while the costs are very real and immediate for the people actually running the shops. doesn't it seem a bit unfair to prioritize these speculative long-term gains over the actual survival of local manufacturing jobs right now?",
